    "work_description": "The City of Portland is currently assisting TriMet with a rezone of these two sites through the Affordable Housing Opportunities Project from EG-1/ EG-1b to CM2 and TriMet would like to better understand the key zoning, building code, infrastructure, and fire code issues that will influence the future development of these subject sites.HOLGATE SITE will consist of the ground-up construction of a new 56 unit multifamily building with a mix of 1-bed, 2-bed and 3-bed units. The 4-story walkup building is organized around a central courtyard with exterior walkways providing access to upper level units. Stormwater will be managed on-site.RHONE SITE will consist of the ground-up construction of a new 30 unit multifamily building with a mix of 1-bed, 2-bed and 3-bed units. The 4-story walkup building is accessed by exterior stairs and walkways. Stormwater will be managed on site.",
